韦力 不要放太多洋葱 Vinnie don't put too many onions in the sauce.

1220
01:20:48,540 --> 01:20:51,130
我没放太多 I didn't put too much onions in Paul.

1221
01:20:51,440 --> 01:20:53,200
只放了三个小的而已 Put three small onions that's all I did.

1222
01:20:53,370 --> 01:20:55,930
三个洋葱 那你放了几罐蕃茄酱 Three onions? How many cans of tomatoes you put in there?

1223
01:20:56,110 --> 01:20:58,840
- 两大罐 - 你不需要放三个洋葱 - I put two big cans. - You don't need three onions.

1224
01:20:59,010 --> 01:21:01,000
强尼煎牛排 Johnny Dio did the meat.

1225
01:21:01,180 --> 01:21:03,780
因为没有烤箱 强尼用平底锅做菜 We had no broiler so Johnny did everything in pans.

1226
01:21:03,950 --> 01:21:06,040
他每次都把屋子里弄得乌烟瘴气 It used to smell up the joint something awful...

1227
01:21:06,220 --> 01:21:09,190
警卫都被熏死了 但他的牛排还真是不错 and the hacks used to die but he still cooked a great steak.

1228
01:21:09,360 --> 01:21:11,880
- 你的牛排要怎么样 - 半生的 - How do you like yours? - Medium rare.

1229
01:21:12,490 --> 01:21:14,620
半生 贵族一个 Medium rare. An aristocrat.

1230
01:21:15,030 --> 01:21:18,790
当你想到监狱 脑中就会出现像电影中那样 You know when you think of prison you get pictures in your mind...

1231
01:21:18,970 --> 01:21:22,600
一排排的人被关在铁栏杆后面 of all those old movies with rows of guys behind bars.

1232
01:21:22,770 --> 01:21:24,670
对兄弟来说不是那样的 It wasn't like that for wiseguys.

1233
01:21:24,840 --> 01:21:27,500
并不是那么槽 除了我很想念吉米 It really wasn't that bad excepting that I missed Jimmy...

1234
01:21:27,670 --> 01:21:29,070
他在亚特兰大受刑 who was doing his time in Atlanta.

1235
01:21:29,240 --> 01:21:31,680
顺便给我两块牛排 好不好 Give me two steaks while you're in there all right?

1236
01:21:33,150 --> 01:21:37,550
在里面的人都是严格地在受刑 混在一起像猪一样 Everyone else in the joint was doing real time mixed together living like pigs.

1237
01:21:37,720 --> 01:21:40,710
可是我们单独生活 一切都由我们控制 But we lived alone. We owned the joint.

1238
